# ai-engineering-harness detail

## Capability Source

Read `.ai-harness/activation.md` first.
Read `.ai-harness/agent-system/SYSTEM_PROMPT.md` and `.ai-harness/agent-system/RESPONSE_CONTRACT.md` before using the harness.
Use `.ai-harness/runtime-commands/` as the local catalog mirror when available.
Use `.ai-harness/commands/` and `.ai-harness/prompt-templates/` for command behavior.

## Provider Capabilities

| Capability | Status |
|---|---|
| Slash commands | fallback only |
| Subagents | rules-based |
| Lifecycle hooks | manual setup |
| Path-scoped rules | native |

## Path-Scoped Rules

Use `.claude/rules/` for files that should only load when matching paths are in context.
Use this detail file for onboarding, setup, and provider questions that do not belong in the always-loaded core rule.

## Forbidden

- Implementing without a clear goal and approved plan
- Shipping without evidence in `VERIFY.md`
- Writing secrets or private business data into `.harness/`
- Continuing after a blocking question
- Inventing command capabilities that are not present in this repo
